Reasoning: The paper deals with the classification and properties of perfect binary one-error-correcting codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the study of Steiner triple systems, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper discusses the construction of codes through switching, which is a topic in coding theory and combinatorics (cs.CC). The study of defining sets of codes and the classification of mixed perfect codes also fall under the scope of coding theory and combinatorics (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of perfect codes, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR).
